column28: I have applied several years. I have never had my portfolio references checked- itâ€™s such a waste of time. The UOW Casper system is lacking. Last year I scored in the highest quintile for Casper. My interview performance was insufficient to get a place. In the interim I undertook interview tutoring to solidify communication of my skills. Concurrently my CASPER quintile dropped to the lowest quintile. Given my interview skills improved sufficiently to get me into Deakin, I would assume my Casper score was better or equal to last year when I was unsuccessful in my interview. Either this years UOW cohort is significantly more emotionally intelligent (hard to accept given 2 years of lockdown), the cohort has been up skilled through tutoring, or the Casper is invalid.
